      "comment": "GO TESS GO (3) led from one spot wider when she won last month at Newcastle and looks close to another success having come from this barrier and recorded a strong performance last start, battling on bravely for a 1.8m third. Draws to enjoy an economical run so could take this out. SIR KNIGHT (7) produced a good performance last time out, finishing third at Newcastle. Drawn to enjoy a cosy run but might need things to go his way at some stage. If he gets the gaps he is capable of taking this out. IMA SHINKANSEN (2) has been solid from the back row at his last couple. He should appreciate a more favourable draw. GREY CADILLAC (10) has claims having placed from this barrier the last time he raced here two back.",
